This paper discusses association rules, which are commonly used in data mining and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on analyzing the statistical significance of association rules, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of database systems (cs.DB). However, the paper also discusses various measures and techniques used in data mining and machine learning, such as confidence, correlation coefficient, and redundancy reduction, which are relevant to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses theoretical results related to statistical significance, which could also be relevant to the subfield of information theory (cs.IT).
